  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for python311",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for python311 fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2025-11468: preserving parens when folding comments in email headers. (bsc#1257029)\n- CVE-2026-0672: rejects control characters in http cookies. (bsc#1257031)\n- CVE-2026-0865: rejecting control characters in wsgiref.headers.Headers, which could be abused for injecting false HTTP headers. (bsc#1257042)\n- CVE-2025-15366: basically the same as the previous patch for IMAP protocol. (bsc#1257044)\n- CVE-2025-15282: basically the same as the previous patch for urllib library. (bsc#1257046)\n- CVE-2025-15367: basically the same as the previous patch for poplib library. (bsc#1257041)\n- CVE-2025-12781: fix decoding with non-standard Base64 alphabet (bsc#1257108)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
